          <h3 id="federated-servers">Federated servers</h3>
          <p>The MEG server is a simple daemon process on an internet connected machine.  The daemon has three primary responsibilities:</p>
          <ol>
            <li>It tracks IP addresses for both the mobile app and client plugins 
            via low bandwidth "heartbeat" requests</li>
            <li>It tracks and distributes public keys for authorized users</li>
            <li>It keeps and distributes revocation lists</li>
          </ol>

          <p>MEG servers must keep an up to date list of all other MEG servers that all of its associated mobile apps have seen.</p>

          <p>A MEG federated server can be fairly transient. All data that is on the server exists somewhere else, so in the event of a server failure, clients can populate data on a new server or fall back to a MEG master server.</p>

          <p>A fourth responsibility is to interface with legacy PGP public key servers to query for public keys and share revocation lists.</p>

