          <h2 id="meg-encrypts">How MEG encrypts a message</h2>
          <ol>
            <li>The client plugin reaches out to the cell phone (as needed, through the server relay) with unencrypted data.</li>
            <li>Data travels between the client application plugin and the cell phone app via an encrypted channel.</li>
            <li>A MEG federated server acts as an intermediary as needed in client -> smartphone communications.</li>
            <li>The cell phone app does the work of encrypting the message, then returning it to the client for storage and delivery.</li>
